  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "There will be a citizens meeting\nheld at Healy's grocery store on\naMllon avenue tonight at 1880.\nThose invited to attend will be resi-\ndents of MallOn, Broadway and\nCollege avenues between A and\nCochran streets. 1t Is understood\nthat a league is to be formed for\nthe purpose of pushing the claims\nOf the residents Of this locality to\npublic improvements. At a former\nmeeting at Mr.. Duffleld's house, Mr..\nHill was elected chairman, and Mr..\nSteffer secretary. One Of the main\npoints at issue is the placing of\nelectric lights at the corners of the\nstreets in that section. They are\nbadly needed at present owing to\nthe steady increase in the number\nof new houses being erected and\nthe poor lighting facilities."
    }
  ]
